<TEXT>
the deadly earthquake that shook thousands of square miles 
around san francisco last week left those who walked away with 
stories to tell here are six personal recollections from the 1989 
earthquake 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
we were just sitting down trying to watch the game funny thing 
is i cant tell you what game i was starting to watch 
the first instinct ive always had with earthquakes is to wait 
for it to pass i didnt want to wait for this one we got out of 
the house in a hot hurry 
i talked to a few other vietnam vets and they all thought they 
were in country for a minute it was like a shock akin to an 
attack 
for the next 45 minutes we checked to see who had gotten hurt 
that store kathys place a general store is the whole community 
thing right there and thats where everybody met 
people worked together well nobody asked questions they just 
did i was running the generator others were stocking the shelves 
people were looking for other people trying to keep an even keel 
it was more like the way things were in country 
the worst of it is the aftershocks are not getting smaller 
theyre getting larger in vietnam you got to where you could 
sleep in a certain state you got to where your body can sleep but 
your minds awake i think thats what everyone is learning to do 
now 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
i was in san jose at a conference by the time i got home boy 
the phones were jammed you couldnt get out my phone wasnt 
working at home 
i hadnt realized how bad my husband was stressed out trying to 
reach me he was in puerto rico i went to work the next day 
because i knew we would have some major work to do with the agency 
once i got to work i didnt even think of my own personal life 
one of the good things you get so busy you dont really think 
about your own being 
when i got home at about 11 that night i was exhausted and went 
to bed and didnt even try to call he called me about 3 in the 
morning and absolutly cried because he was so upset i said i was 
really sorry because i knew i was ok i just was so busy trying to 
organize the workers here that i didnt even think that you would 
be worried about me so he was horrified 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
i was waiting for the world series to come on i was sitting on 
the bed just kicked back i was so relaxed and all of a sudden i 
heard this sound it was like a bang and i thought oh 
another little earthquake cool but then it felt like a 
giant took the building and shook it first i looked up and i saw 
the ceiling i mean the whole ceiling came down i mean all of it 
at once i said oh no 
then it shook so hard that the floor cracked it more than 
just cracked its like it broke snapped in half thats when i 
really got scared ive been through earthquakes before but not 
like this one 
i was running for the door because it kept shaking and they say 
get under a doorway i did that but that didnt work everything 
just rumbled so i ran out of the building fast 
everything was falling the walls were cracking everywhere 
one weird thing though hardly any glass broke mostly the wood 
and plaster which maybe in one way was lucky 
i thought is this my last day on this earth 
they say theres going to be one bigger than this one lord help 
us all really 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
ill never forget where i bought my watchband 
i was in woolworths at market and powell when the quake hit i 
just slammed my money down on the counter and ran i said to 
myself i dont want to die in woolworths 
when the building started shaking at first i thought it might 
be from the muni trains underneath for a second i thought the 
shaking was over then there was a boom and it was like a giant 
had picked the building up and slammed it to the ground 
i almost knocked over a little old lady on the way to the 
street there was broken glass out there and a lot of dust flying 
then i went to my buildings to see if anyone was trapped in 
elevators i worked until 2 oclock and they called me at 530 
or 6 in the morning to come back in to work we all got about three 
or four hours sleep those first two nights 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
i was taking a nap actually christopher her 4yearold son 
was watching cartoons i heard him scream that woke me up and 
everything was really shaking 
he ran into the bedroom i grabbed him and lay down on top of 
him the first thing i thought was my god this is it i heard 
things crashing around i looked out the bedroom door and saw my 
refrigerator come out of the kitchen into the living room when 
everything stopped i packed everyone a change of clothes and left 
i didnt know what else to do 
it was like being in a tunnel underneath a freight train 
christopher described it as the planet was falling apart he 
thought it was the whole world he wanted me to call his 
grandmother in alabama and make sure they were ok 
</TEXT>
