the decision by three north african girls to wear 
moslem head coverings to junior high school has exploded into an 
intense national debate over religion in public schools 
at issue is the secularity of education enshrined in french law 
since the official separation of the church and the state in this 
largely roman catholic country in 1905 
some argue that wearing the hijab a scarf that covers the 
hair ears and neck is tantamount to proselytism 
about 400 people shouting god is great in arabic 
