repairs to the san franciscooakland bay 
bridge began sunday when a huge crane hefted half of the damaged 
upper deck section off the lower roadway and smoothly lowered it 
onto a barge 200 feet below 
but todays task just the beginning of work expected to take at 
least a month offers no relief to the gridlock expected when the 
work week resumes monday 
it was unclear whether officials would try to remove a second 
100ton section of collapsed roadway sunday or wait until monday 
officials say it will cost up to 1 million to repair the 
53yearold bridge damaged spectacularly in tuesdays earthquake 
nationally broadcast pictures of the broken bridge with the 
upper deck dangling like an open trap door provided the first 
graphic illustration of the magnitude of the quake one woman died 
when she drove her car into the gap 
the bridge had also been in the logo created for the 1989 world 
series between the san francisco giants and the oakland athletics 
since it links the two cities but its closure contributed to 
sundays decision to delay resumption of the championship until 
friday as officials attempt to reduce traffic problems 
the 85milelong bridge carries 260000 vehicles per day and 
the only alternatives are other jammed bridges overloaded mass 
transit systems and a makeshift fleet of ferry boats 
the dangerous and painstaking task of lifting the heavy section 
of roadway out of the damaged area and then lowering it to the 
barge at bay level went without a hitch sunday 
good planning said state department of transportation 
